CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 20, 1953, page 23, reads: "Business Leader - William Goode, prominent proprietor of the two Goode Pharmacies, gave away several wonderful prizes from this magnetic display which created much interest in McKesson's Drug Products. He was assisted by his charming wife, Mrs. Sarah Goode; Charylene Dudley, Yvonne Nicholas and Eugene Douglas (not shown)."
TitMainTitle: Goode Pharmacy display booth with picket fence surrounding tables with pharmacy products, in Ammon Center for the 1953 Pittsburgh Courier Home Service Fair
